{"id": "EUVD-2022-55354", "enisaUuid": "e3de45b2-ead8-3b01-9ee5-f8b512f093ca", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmm/damon/reclaim: fix potential memory leak in damon_reclaim_init()\n\ndamon_reclaim_init() allocates a memory chunk for ctx with\ndamon_new_ctx().  When damon_select_ops() fails, ctx is not released,\nwhich will lead to a memory leak.\n\nWe should release the ctx with damon_destroy_ctx() when damon_select_ops()\nfails to fix the memory leak.", "datePublished": "2025-06-18T12:30:47", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-18T03:31:13", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9d3e9e1e0856f4c905bbb870f16f42ae72477071", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/700aa4e11a3c4d2a44d06758db431a013d9e1b61", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/188043c7f4f2bd662f2a55957d684fffa543e600", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50088"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50088"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "053842f1-ffad-3712-8992-6b423d5fafbb", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "18656e40-fb20-390e-8447-7be0da3e2c1c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4d69c3457821100a39fa8c6e0c23ed910bb6c29d <9d3e9e1e0856f4c905bbb870f16f42ae72477071"}, {"id": "341d2f1a-3056-31e0-8e4b-48e320c7db55", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4d69c3457821100a39fa8c6e0c23ed910bb6c29d <700aa4e11a3c4d2a44d06758db431a013d9e1b61"}, {"id": "37826010-c1ca-33b4-8fd7-c3c787a617fb", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0"}, {"id": "41509f9c-a845-3a84-9291-0493b108143c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19.2"}, {"id": "55645e5d-a1cf-3741-b40c-91e837a115e5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4d69c3457821100a39fa8c6e0c23ed910bb6c29d <188043c7f4f2bd662f2a55957d684fffa543e600"}, {"id": "67936258-3371-3843-bc0f-f1d382192d6d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.18.18"}, {"id": "98ba0